00:19:20,274 --> 00:19:23,874
Don't you think the grandfather will stay away for a long time?

283
00:19:23,874 --> 00:19:26,874
Nothing will happen to him, will it?

284
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:28,830
I don't know.

285
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:30,830
I don't know.

286
00:20:18,002 --> 00:20:20,002
That's Joseph's grave!

287
00:20:20,002 --> 00:20:21,502
You think so?

288
00:20:21,502 --> 00:20:23,002
But of course!

289
00:20:23,002 --> 00:20:25,002
-Almi! -Grandfather!

290
00:20:35,502 --> 00:20:37,502
Yes, they're coming over there!

291
00:20:37,502 --> 00:20:40,502
-Grandfather! -He found the two jellies!

292
00:20:40,502 --> 00:20:41,502
Hurrah!

293
00:20:41,502 --> 00:20:43,502
Grandfather, you're finally here!

294
00:20:43,502 --> 00:20:45,502
I was so afraid of you!

295
00:20:45,502 --> 00:20:47,502
Go slowly, Grandfather!

296
00:20:48,882 --> 00:20:50,882
I'll come and help you!

297
00:20:52,882 --> 00:20:55,382
We also set a pot of milk on fire for you!

298
00:20:55,382 --> 00:20:58,382
In which hole did they bury the two of them?

299
00:21:05,398 --> 00:21:10,398
Was it dangerous for you? Did you get off the road because it took so long?

300
00:21:10,398 --> 00:21:13,398
No, I had Joseph.

301
00:21:13,398 --> 00:21:17,398
Everything went well, don't be afraid, my child.

302
00:21:17,398 --> 00:21:22,398
I'm so happy. If hunters come again, we won't let them go.

303
00:21:27,932 --> 00:21:34,932
Peter spent the night on the hut and when the sun rose the next morning, he and
Heidi roamed down into the valley

304
00:21:35,932 --> 00:21:38,932
Goodbye grandfather, until tonight

305
00:21:38,932 --> 00:21:43,932
The two hunters stayed at the Almöhi for a while to get rid of their fright

306
00:21:45,932 --> 00:21:50,932
Almöhi, I'm sorry, we've been pretty stupid

307
00:21:50,932 --> 00:21:53,932
We behaved like little children

308
00:21:55,116 --> 00:21:59,116
Children behave more reasonably, they listen

309
00:21:59,116 --> 00:22:04,116
I'm not used to it from you, you're all like that, you believe you belong to the
world

310
00:22:08,116 --> 00:22:12,116
If Heidi hadn't been there, the Alp Öhi wouldn't have looked for the two of them

311
00:22:12,116 --> 00:22:15,116
But that's why he didn't have a bad conscience for a long time

312
00:22:15,116 --> 00:22:21,116
He couldn't do anything with these Steters, who make the mountain world insecure
with their guns at the weekend

313
00:22:21,116 --> 00:22:24,460
He just didn't like them and he didn't keep it a secret

314
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:28,460
He knew that he couldn't forbid them to hunt when they had a hunting license

315
00:22:28,460 --> 00:22:31,460
But he himself didn't want to have anything to do with it

316
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:35,460
Grandmother, we're here!

317
00:22:50,422 --> 00:22:54,422
When the sun was shining, Heidi had a lot of fun in the snow.

318
00:22:54,422 --> 00:23:00,422
She wandered with Joseph through the white winter landscape and took a lot of
time to teach her beloved tree how to speak.

319
00:23:00,422 --> 00:23:04,422
Even if she herself didn't really believe that she could do it.

320
00:23:04,422 --> 00:23:07,422
She was on her feet all day to discover something new.

321
00:23:07,422 --> 00:23:12,422
And on one of these streaks she saw the first signs of spring.

322
00:23:12,422 --> 00:23:16,422
Of course she had to describe Peter's grandmother in every detail.

323
00:23:16,422 --> 00:23:19,500
But that wasn't the smallest detail in her vivid description.

324
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:24,260
She told us about the flowers and the melting water, about the Alp Oehi and
about her animals.

325
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:27,260
But we want to tell you about that in our next story.

326
00:23:28,674 --> 00:23:37,174
Heidi, Heidi, your world are the mountains.

327
00:23:37,174 --> 00:23:45,174
Heidi, Heidi, because up here you are at home.

328
00:23:45,174 --> 00:23:58,174
Heidi, Heidi, come home, find your happiness, come back home.

